{"id":22691,"url":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Urbain_Grandier","text":"Urbain Grandier (born 1590 in Bou\u00E8re, Mayenne, France; died April 18,1634 in Loudun, France) was a free-thinking cleric. A satirical publication against Richelieu was attributed to him. After this, Pierre-Martin de Laubardement, a statesman was charged to lead the process against Grandier in 1633. He was charged of having bewitched the ursuline nuns of Loudun. They became obsessed by him. His friend, Claude Quillet agreed to defend him in court, but without success.\nHe was condemned to burn at the stake as a witch in 1634.","categories":[],"infobox_types":[],"annotations":[{"uri":"1590","surface_form":"1590","offset":22},{"uri":"Bou%C3%A8re","surface_form":"Bou\u00E8re","offset":30},{"uri":"Mayenne","surface_form":"Mayenne","offset":38},{"uri":"France","surface_form":"France","offset":47},{"uri":"April_18","surface_form":"April 18","offset":60},{"uri":"1634","surface_form":"1634","offset":69},{"uri":"Loudun","surface_form":"Loudun","offset":77},{"uri":"Satire","surface_form":"satirical","offset":123},{"uri":"Richelieu","surface_form":"Richelieu","offset":153},{"uri":"Attribution","surface_form":"attributed","offset":167},{"uri":"Pierre-Martin_de_Laubardement","surface_form":"Pierre-Martin de Laubardement","offset":198},{"uri":"Statesman","surface_form":"statesman","offset":231},{"uri":"Process","surface_form":"process","offset":265},{"uri":"Witchcraft","surface_form":"bewitched","offset":324},{"uri":"Ursuline","surface_form":"ursuline","offset":338},{"uri":"Nun","surface_form":"nun","offset":347},{"uri":"Obsession","surface_form":"obsessed","offset":375},{"uri":"Claude_Quillet","surface_form":"Claude Quillet","offset":404},{"uri":"Court","surface_form":"court","offset":443},{"uri":"Witch","surface_form":"witch","offset":514}]}